-1.title: Banana Quest
-1.plot: Thinking Nesmith is ill, Sheen, Doppy and Aseefa go on a harrowing quest to find the only thing that can cure him: a banana.

1.title: Pilot
1.plot: Sheen ignores some notes in Jimmy's lab and he blasts off into space and lands on a strange planet named "Zeenu" and destroys Dorkus's house. When he gets there he meets the Emporer and his daughter, Princess Oomlet who says that she loves Sheen. He also meets Dorkus. He meets a talking chimpanzee from earth named Nesmith. He meets other aliens including one that looked like his old friend Carl from Jimmy Neutron all in one day!

2.title: Is This Cute?/The Boy Next Dorkus
2.plot: The Emperor tries to prepare Sheen for a visit from Boh-Rok the Destroyer, the most powerful and horrible creature in all of Zeenu./Dorkus vows revenge when his new next door neighbor Sheen upstages his elegant game night with a wild raging party.

3.title: What's Up, Chock?/Joust Friends
3.plot: Sheen and the guys infiltrate a vicious pack of Chocktows to help Aseefa find her missing pet, Chock-Chock./Princess Oom's gigantic, two-headed ex-boyfriend, Grish the Beautiful, challenges Sheen to a battle of honor.

4.title: Sheen for a Day/Well Bread Man
4.plot: Sheen accidentally gives Princess Oom the most important part of his rocket ship and has to find a way to get it back.Seeing an opportunity to destroy Sheen, Dorkus volunteers to train him for the "Manhood Trial by Fire."

5.title: Cutting the Ultra-Cord/Trial by Jerry
5.plot: Nesmith and Doppy are worried about Sheen's erratic behavior. Dorkus suggests therapy by man-eating Fusterbeest./Sheen introduces the justice system to Zeenu when he has to defend Nesmith who has been accused of eating the Emperor's favorite pet.

6.title: Keeping Up with the Gronzes/Torzilla
6.plot: Obsessed with setting world records, Sheen challenges competitive librarian acrobats to a book-stacking competition./Sheen grows a tortilla monster that threatens the city

7.title: Thanksgetting/There's Something About Scary
7.plot: Sheen invents an "all get, no give" holiday that nearly destroys him./Aseefa is imprisoned for making a scary face, and it's up to Sheen to break her out.

8.title: Act I, Sheen I/Money Suits Sheen
8.plot: Sheen and Aseefa star in Dorkus' play, unaware that it's been riddled with booby traps./Sheen sells a non-existent product to the masses so he can build a suit made of money, but his scheme backfires when his customers show up at his house for the goods.

9.title: Washing My Sheen/Stuck in the Riddle with You
9.plot: Sheen vows to never bathe again and accidentally attracts a horde of destructive, filth-loving beasts.Sheen has to use his matchless wit to rid Zeenu and save his friends from a carnivorous, pretentious plant called the Dentamental.

10.title: Chock Around the Clock/The Oomlick Maneuver
10.plot: While pet-sitting, Sheen accidentally gets Aseefa's pet Chocktow caught by Animal Control and has to rescue him before she returns./In an attempt to stop Princess Oom from liking and licking him, Sheen tries to get her back together with her ex-boyfriend.

11.title: Ooze on First/Monster-Fighting Combat Strike Force
11.plot: Sheen teaches Zeenu his version of baseball.Doppy's parents fear their son is becoming too courageous when he and Sheen form the Monster-Fighting Combat Strike Force.

12.title: To Chill a Mocking Blurg/Now You Sheen It
12.plot: The Emperor's Royal Ball of Compliments quickly turns into a Hall of Insults as Sheen and his friends are plagued by a flock of bird-like, rowdy, mocking blurgs. Sheen puts on a magic show that actually makes people disappear.

13.title: Desperate Houseguests/Nesvidanya
13.plot: Sheen helps Doppy's parents rid their house of an unwanted guest.Sheen has to rescue Nesmith from a mythical white-haired creature, the Boopenfoofer.

14.title: Sheen Says/Hippocratic Oaf
14.plot: Chaos ensues when the Emperor leaves town and puts Sheen in charge of the kingdom.Sheen becomes a doctor and sets up a clinic in Zeenu.

15.title: ExpreSheenism/Gotta Go
15.plot: Sheen's starts a new art movement only to have it take over his life.Sheen has to "go" but he doesn't want Aseefa to know.

16.title: Well Oiled Fighting Ma-Sheen/Dorkus in Chains
16.plot: Sheen must train the Emperor's Guard to prepare for emergence of a legendary beast, the Londar.Accidentally chained to each other, Sheen and Dorkus are trapped underground and must work together to find a way out.

17.title: He Went Hataway/Tongue-Tied
17.plot: Sheen uses his master detective skills to find Nesmith's missing hat.Sheen gets stuck to Oom's tongue and must find a way to free himself.

18.title: Nesmith is Spoken For/Feeling Roovy
18.plot: When Nesmith loses his ability to speak, Sheen must save the planet using the awesome power of ventriloquism.Sheen helps Aseefa get her Roove back.

19.title: Shave the Last Dance for Me/Berry Big Mess
19.plot: In order to help Aseefa, Sheen purchases a black market mustache and must deal with the consequences when it gets out of control.Sheen eats a berry that makes him huge and hazardous.

20.title: Scape Doat/Haute CuiSheen
20.plot: Sheen passes the blame on breaking the Doppweiller's figurine collection to Doppy's new pet, Doaty, and must make things right before Doaty is sent to the pound.

21.title: MetamorphoSheen/MiSheen Impossible
21.plot: Sheen has to figure out a way to lead the Celebration of Legs Parade despite the fact that he's turning into an eelSheen and Nesmith rescue Doppy from a group of gloop thieves, the Gashlubbs.

23.title: Sheen Racer/QuaranSheen
23.plot: Sheen enters a flying bug saucer race.To avoid Oom's advances, Sheen fakes an illness called "dance fever" that actually starts spreading to other Zeenuians.

25.title: Raging Belle/Breath Wish
25.plot: Sheen helps Aseefa get through her one night of Tahlak Pow where she turns into a vicious, rampaging beast.Sheen tries to keep Zeenu safe from Baby Arms Banarog, a desperado with evil breath.

26.title: Blunderings/Dawn of the Wedge
26.plot: To improve Zeenu's government, Sheen introduces the concept of Clown College.Zeenu is attacked a swarm of wedgie-giving barbarians and it's up to Sheen to stop them.

imdb.plot outline: Sheen Estevez, our protagonist, despite a warning from his friend Jimmy Neutron about a button on his ship presses it to see what happens. He finds himself on another planet. No humans... The planet is ruled by "The Emperor". Sheen is pursued by Dorkis, our adorable clueless bad guy, who has intentions of capturing our protagonist. Sheen is accompanied by Nesmith, a talking talking chimpanzee who has also found himself marooned upon this planet.
imdb.title: Planet Sheen
plot: Sheen Estevez, our protagonist, despite a warning from his friend Jimmy Neutron about a button on his ship presses it to see what happens. He finds himself on another planet. No humans... The planet is ruled by "The Emperor". Sheen is pursued by Dorkis, our adorable clueless bad guy, who has intentions of capturing our protagonist. Sheen is accompanied by Nesmith, a talking talking chimpanzee who has also found himself marooned upon this planet.::Luca Elliot Sanderson (and edited by Nevyn Hira)
synopsis: An annoying boy Sheen Estevez reads a warning by his friend Jimmy Neutron and finds out he accidentally clicked the button on Jimmy's ship that sends him to a weird planet where no human awaits Zeenu. Then Sheen crashes there and see's a unatural emperor who rules the world. Then a bad guy called Dorkus try'es to capture Sheen and keep him in his secret lair. Sheen meets a not so obsessed monkey called Nesmith. Nesmith is the shyest guy in the episodes. He doesn't like getting annoyed by Sheen of all his jokes. Sheen stays at the planet to fix his ship back to earth but finding out that may take a while for Sheen to do so Nesmith helps out. After many days of hard work it's no use. Then Sheen stays at the planet with his new friends: A weird longed tongue lady called Oom, A Carl type snail Doppy and a nice girl that Sheen meets called Aseefa. Dorku's friend Pinter doesn't care about what Dorkus says. Then Sheen explores an amazing adventure just for him and his friends
